comment: i think efficiency dropped with temp drop of mash (blickman doesnt hold well, have to add insulation i got from siegel), went down to 140 by the end. no airlock activity but its a small beer and a bucket so not worried. sitting at 49 on outside of carboy for 4 days. pitched 2 11 gram packets so plenty of yeast!
1 week in, 50-52 on bucket, smells really nice and malty, rich. im excited.
smelled great during transfer, upon further reading i think efficiency also dropped due to too small a mash (5 gal batch in my 15 gal blich). any how finished at 1008 for a 4.73 abv

really nice maltiness, good aroma, a  bit of sweetness, dry finish, (mash dropped to 140 by end of mash), i think it would be better if the mash stayed at the correct temp (154ish), maybe some munich next time? see the ingrediants above. taste again after it lagers more
really coming around nicely now, lagered for over a month. great malt and aroma.
really amazing toasty aroma, perfect color, flavor could use a bit of crystal and munich in my mind. not too much. i think 2.5 to 5% medium crystal and 10% munich.
won 2nd or 3rd in lagers at another clubs comp, rob and i went up to ceremony
